item.description:
 &lt;p&gt;As for worrying about what other people might think, forget it. They aren’t concerned about you. They’re too busy worrying about what you and other people think of them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The greatest of follies is to sacrifice health for any other kind of happiness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes life is going to hit you in the head with a brick. Don’t lose faith.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are two means of refuge from the miseries of life: music and cats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“Careful with fire” is good advice we know. “Careful with words” is ten times doubly so.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fight for your opinions, but do not believe that they contain the whole truth, or the only truth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life gives you a comb after you lose your hair.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’m going to memorize your name and throw my head away.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a sacredness in tears. They are not the mark of weakness, but of power.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hypocrisy can afford to be magnificent in its promises, for never intending to go beyond promise, it costs nothing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your pain is the breaking of the shell that encloses your understanding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Logic merely enables one to be wrong with authority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constantly talking isn’t necessarily communicating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nothing can cure the soul but the senses, just as nothing can cure the senses but the soul.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another belief of mine: that everyone else my age is an adult, whereas I am merely in disguise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To obtain a man’s opinion of you, make him mad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In great attempts, it is even glorious to fail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is easier to resist at the beginning than at the end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The fact that an opinion has been widely held is no evidence whatever that it is not utterly absurd.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Begin at the beginning, and go on until you come to the end; then stop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The beauty of a woman is not in the clothes she wears, the figure that she carries or the way she combs her hair.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we obtain too cheaply, we esteem too lightly; it’s dearness only that gives everything its value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home is not where you live but where they understand you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is certainly desirable to be well descended, but the glory belongs to our ancestors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone can do any amount of work provided it isn’t the work he is supposed to be doing at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You cannot shake hands with a clenched fist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes I have thought it would be an excellent rule to live each day as if we should die tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don’t try to win a friend by presenting gifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The more you experience and appreciate the goodness of life, the more there is to be lived.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What greater blessing than to be with those you love, and to feel that every heart beats in harmony.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Love is a choice. It is a conscious commitment. It is something you choose to make work every day with a person who has chosen the same thing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not I - not anyone else, can travel that road for you, You must travel it for yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The golden rule is that there are no golden rules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our anxiety does not come from thinking about the future, but from wanting to control it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Things change. And friends leave. Life doesn’t stop for anybody.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The way you treat yourself sets the standard for others.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To avoid criticism, do nothing, say nothing and be nothing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most wasted of days is one without laughter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The power of imagination created the illusion that my vision went much farther than the naked eye could actually see.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nothing is so strong as gentleness, nothing so gentle as real strength.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No winter lasts forever; no spring skips its turn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What is essential is invisible to the eye.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The quieter you become, the more you can hear.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no greater agony than bearing an untold story inside you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You and I who still enjoy fairy tales have less reason to wish actual childhood back. We have kept its pleasures and added some grown-up ones as well. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are two ways of getting home; and one of them is to stay there. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are far, far better things ahead than any we leave behind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Waiting is painful. Forgetting is painful. But not knowing which to do is the worst kind of suffering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is only one success - to be able to spend your life in your own way. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Either write things worth reading, or do things worth writing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s no use going back to yesterday, because I was a different person then. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The true triumph of reason is that it enables us to get along with those who do not possess it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health is the pillar of the soul and an important foundation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Destiny is like a dust storm; you have nowhere to hide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Curious things, habits. People themselves never knew they had them. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can feel pain, you are alive; if you can feel the pain of others, you are human.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are three classes of people: those who see, those who see when they are shown, those who do not see.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be without some of the things you want is an indispensable part of happiness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The dignity and glory of the person lies not in sophistication but in honesty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is difficult to find happiness within oneself, but it is impossible to find it anywhere else.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will never have what you like until you learn to like what you have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is in our faults and mistakes, not in our virtues, that we touch each other and find resonance. Our essence lies in our absurdities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The only true wisdom is in knowing you know nothing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What lies behind us and what lies before us are tiny matters compared to what lies within us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life isn’t about waiting for the storm to pass. It’s about learning how to dance in the rain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We must accept finite disappointment, but we must never lose infinite hope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every snowflake is a masterpiece of patience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Courage is grace under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We don’t see things as they are, we see them as we are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The art of being wise is knowing what to overlook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The past is a place of reference, not a place of residence; the past is a place of learning, not a place of living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The greatest wealth is to live content with little.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We either make ourselves miserable, or we make ourselves strong. The amount of work is the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I would rather sit on a pumpkin, and have it all to myself, than be crowded on a velvet cushion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do not wait for leaders; do it alone, person to person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No one can make you feel inferior without your consent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He who is of a calm and happy nature will hardly feel the pressure of age, but to him who is of an opposite disposition, youth and age are equally a burden.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You run from one place to another, but you are still you. You can’t escape from your body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A lie can travel halfway around the world while the truth is still putting on its shoes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have approximate answers and possible beliefs and different degrees of certainty about different things… It doesn’t frighten me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No man is really happy or safe without a hobby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding is the first step to acceptance, and only with acceptance can there be recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can never know things as they are in themselves, only as they appear to us. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are all like the bright moon; we still have our darker side.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The content of your character is your choice. Day by day, what you choose, what you think and what you do is who you become.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One should sympathize with the color, the beauty, the joy of life. The less said about life’s sores the better.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do not say a little in many words but a great deal in a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can resist everything except temptation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The soul becomes dyed with the color of its thoughts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We may give advice, but we can’t give conduct.&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;h4 id=&#34;Excuse-me&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Excuse-me&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Excuse me&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Excuse me&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Excuse me!&lt;br&gt;Yes?&lt;br&gt;Is this your handbag?&lt;br&gt;Pardon?&lt;br&gt;Is this your handbag?&lt;br&gt;Yes, it is.&lt;br&gt;Thank you very much.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Sorry-sir&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Sorry-sir&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Sorry sir&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Sorry sir&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;My coat and my umbrella please.&lt;br&gt;Here is my tickets.&lt;br&gt;Thank you, sir.&lt;br&gt;Number five.&lt;br&gt;Here’s your umbrella and your coat.&lt;br&gt;This is not my umbrella.&lt;br&gt;Sorry sir.&lt;br&gt;Is this your umbrella?&lt;br&gt;No, it isn’t.&lt;br&gt;Is this it?&lt;br&gt;Yes, it is.&lt;br&gt;Thank you very much.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Nice-to-meet-you&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Nice-to-meet-you&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Nice to meet you&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Nice to meet you&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Good morning.&lt;br&gt;Good morning, Mr. Blake.&lt;br&gt;This is Miss Sophie Dupont.&lt;br&gt;Sophie is a new student. She is French.&lt;br&gt;Sophie, this is Hans. He is German.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you.&lt;br&gt;And this is Naoko. She’s Japanese.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you.&lt;br&gt;And this is Chang-woo. He’s Korean.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you.&lt;br&gt;And this is Luming. He is Chinese.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you.&lt;br&gt;And this is Xiaohui. Shie’s Chinese, too.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Are-you-a-teacher&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Are-you-a-teacher&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Are you a teacher&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Are you a teacher&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;I am a new student. My name’s Robert.&lt;br&gt;Nice to meet you. My name’s Sophie.&lt;br&gt;Are you French?&lt;br&gt;Yes, I am.&lt;br&gt;Are you French too?&lt;br&gt;No, I am not.&lt;br&gt;What nationality are you?&lt;br&gt;I’m Italian.&lt;br&gt;Are you a teacher?&lt;br&gt;No, I’m not.&lt;br&gt;What’s your job?&lt;br&gt;I’m a keyboard operator.&lt;br&gt;What’s your job?&lt;br&gt;I’m an engineer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;How-are-you-today&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#How-are-you-today&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;How are you today&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;How are you today&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hello, Helen.&lt;br&gt;Hi, Steven.&lt;br&gt;How are you today?&lt;br&gt;I’m very well, thank you. And you?&lt;br&gt;How is Tony?&lt;br&gt;He’s fine, thanks. How’s Emma?&lt;br&gt;She’s very well, too, Helen.&lt;br&gt;Goodbye, Helen. Nice to see you.&lt;br&gt;Nice to see you, too, Steven.&lt;br&gt;Goodbye.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Is-this-your-shirt&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Is-this-your-shirt&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Is this your shirt&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Is this your shirt&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Whose shirt is that?&lt;br&gt;Is this your shirt, Dave?&lt;br&gt;No. Sir. It’s not my shirt.&lt;br&gt;This is my shirt. My shirt’s blue.&lt;br&gt;Is this shirt Tim’s?&lt;br&gt;Perhaps it is, sir. Tim’s shirt’s white.&lt;br&gt;Tim!&lt;br&gt;Yes, sir?&lt;br&gt;Is this your shirt?&lt;br&gt;Yes, sir.&lt;br&gt;Here you are. Catch!&lt;br&gt;Thank you. sir.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;A-New-Dress&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#A-New-Dress&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;A New Dress&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;A New Dress&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;What color’s your new dress?&lt;br&gt;It’s green.&lt;br&gt;Come upstairs and see it.&lt;br&gt;Thank you.&lt;br&gt;Look! Here it is!&lt;br&gt;That’s a nice dress. It’s very smart.&lt;br&gt;My hat’s new, too.&lt;br&gt;What colour is it?&lt;br&gt;It’s the same colour. It’s green, too.&lt;br&gt;That is a lovely hat!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;You-passports-please&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#You-passports-please&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;You passports please&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;You passports please&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you Swedish?&lt;br&gt;No, we are not. We are Danish.&lt;br&gt;Are your friends Danish, too?&lt;br&gt;No, they aren’t. They are Norwegian.&lt;br&gt;Your passports, please.&lt;br&gt;Here they are.&lt;br&gt;Are these your cases?&lt;br&gt;No, they aren’t.&lt;br&gt;Our cases are brown. Here they are.&lt;br&gt;Are you tourists?&lt;br&gt;Yes, we are.&lt;br&gt;Are your friends tourists too?&lt;br&gt;Yes, they are.&lt;br&gt;That’s fine.&lt;br&gt;Thank you very much.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;How-do-you-do&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#How-do-you-do&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;How do you do&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;How do you do&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Come and meet our  employees, Mr. Richards.&lt;br&gt;Thank you, Mr, Jackson.&lt;br&gt;This is Nicola Grey, and this is Claire Taylor.&lt;br&gt;How do you do?&lt;br&gt;Those women are very hard-working.&lt;br&gt;What are their jobs?&lt;br&gt;They’re keyboard operators.&lt;br&gt;This is Michael Baker, and this is Jeremy Short.&lt;br&gt;How do you do?&lt;br&gt;They aren’t very busy!&lt;br&gt;What are their jobs?&lt;br&gt;They’re sales reps.&lt;br&gt;They are very lazy.&lt;br&gt;Who is this young man?&lt;br&gt;This is Jim.&lt;br&gt;He is our office assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Tired-and-thirsty&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Tired-and-thirsty&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Tired and thirsty&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Tired and thirsty&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;What’s the matter, children?&lt;br&gt;We are tired and thirsty, Mum.&lt;br&gt;Sit down here.&lt;br&gt;Are you all right now?&lt;br&gt;No, we aren’t.&lt;br&gt;Look!&lt;br&gt;There’s an ice cream man.&lt;br&gt;Two ice cream please.&lt;br&gt;Here you are, children.&lt;br&gt;Thanks, Mum.&lt;br&gt;These ice creams are nice.&lt;br&gt;Are you all right now?&lt;br&gt;Yes, we are, thank you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Which-book&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Which-book&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Which book&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Which book&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Give me a book please, Jane.&lt;br&gt;Which book?&lt;br&gt;This one?&lt;br&gt;No, not that one. The red one.&lt;br&gt;This one?&lt;br&gt;Yes, please.&lt;br&gt;Here you are.&lt;br&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Which-glasses&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Which-glasses&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Which glasses&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Which glasses&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Give me some glasses please, Jane.&lt;br&gt;which glasses?&lt;br&gt;These glasses?&lt;br&gt;No, not these. The ones on the shelf.&lt;br&gt;These?&lt;br&gt;Yes, please.&lt;br&gt;Here you are.&lt;br&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;Mrs-Smith’s-kitchen&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Mrs-Smith’s-kitchen&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Mrs Smith’s kitchen&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Mrs Smith’s kitchen&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mrs. Smith’s kitchen is small.&lt;br&gt;There is a refrigerator in the kitchen.&lt;br&gt;The refrigerator is white.&lt;br&gt;It is on the right.&lt;br&gt;There is an electric cooker in the kitchen.&lt;br&gt;The cooker is blue.&lt;br&gt;It is on the left.&lt;br&gt;There is a table in the middle of the room.&lt;br&gt;There is a bottle on the table.&lt;br&gt;The bottle is empty.&lt;br&gt;There is a cup on the table, too.&lt;br&gt;The cup is clean.&lt;/p&gt;
